The huge €222 million transfer is the largest in football history.
Previously, the record was for Manchester United, which cost €105 million last summer for French Paul Pogba.
The Spanish league held back the move earlier on Thursday when it rejected Neymar's first payment attempt.
Under the league's rules, a buying club cannot pay the buy-out price directly to the seller, but the player must buy out their contract, which is done by recycling money through the league.
In practice, PSG has paid the amount to Neymar and his representatives, who delivered the money through the league to Barcelona.
Neymar is expected to arrive in Paris on Friday.
He will possibly be introduced to a new home audience at the PSG season opening against Amiens on Saturday.
